# Demonstrate upper asymptote concept
cat("\n=== UPPER ASYMPTOTE TESIRININ DEMONSTRASIYASI ===\n")
## 
## === UPPER ASYMPTOTE TESIRININ DEMONSTRASIYASI ===
demonstrate_upper_asymptote_effect <- function() {
  theta_range <- seq(-4, 4, by = 0.1)
  
  # Fixed parameters
  discrimination <- 1.5
  difficulty <- 0
  guessing <- 0.2
  
  # Different upper asymptote values
  d_values <- c(1.0, 0.95, 0.90, 0.85, 0.80)
  colors <- c("blue", "green", "orange", "red", "purple")
  
  # Plot comparison
  plot(theta_range, prob_4pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, guessing, 1.0),
       type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "blue",
       main = "Upper Asymptote Tesiri: Muxtelif d Deyerleri (a=1.5, b=0, c=0.2)",
       xlab = "Theta", ylab = "P(X = 1 | theta)",
       ylim = c(0, 1), xlim = c(-4, 4))
  
  for(i in 1:length(d_values)) {
    prob <- prob_4pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, guessing, d_values[i])
    lines(theta_range, prob, lwd = 3, col = colors[i])
    
    # Mark asymptotes
    abline(h = d_values[i], lty = 3, col = colors[i])
    if(d_values[i] < 1.0) {
      text(3, d_values[i] + 0.02, paste("d =", d_values[i]), 
           col = colors[i], cex = 0.8)
    }
  }
  
  # Mark lower asymptote
  abline(h = guessing, lty = 2, col = "gray")
  text(-3, guessing + 0.02, paste("c =", guessing), col = "gray", cex = 0.8)
  
  legend("right", paste("d =", d_values), col = colors, lwd = 3, cex = 0.8)
  grid(TRUE)
  
  cat("Key Insights:\n")
  cat("1. Upper asymptote d mehdudlasdirÄ±r maximum performance\n")
  cat("2. d < 1.0 yuksek ability ucun plateau yaradir\n")
  cat("3. Effective range (d-c) azalir d azaldiqca\n")
  cat("4. Discrimination effectiveness azalir\n\n")
  
  return(list(theta = theta_range, d_values = d_values))
}

upper_demo <- demonstrate_upper_asymptote_effect()

  print(d_realism_analysis)
  
  return(d_realism_analysis)
}

  guessing <- 0.15
  
  # Range of d values - avoid RColorBrewer dependency
  d_values <- c(1.0, 0.95, 0.90, 0.85, 0.80, 0.75)
  colors <- c("blue", "green", "orange", "red", "purple", "brown")
  
  # Create comprehensive plot
  plot(theta_range, prob_4pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, guessing, 1.0),
       type = "l", lwd = 3, col = colors[1],
       main = "d Parametrinin ICC-ye Tesiri (a=1.2, b=0, c=0.15)",
       xlab = "Theta", ylab = "P(X = 1 | theta)",
       ylim = c(0, 1), xlim = c(-4, 4))
  
  # Plot all curves
  for(i in 1:length(d_values)) {
    prob <- prob_4pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, guessing, d_values[i])
    lines(theta_range, prob, lwd = 3, col = colors[i])
    
    # Mark upper asymptotes
    abline(h = d_values[i], lty = 3, col = colors[i])
    text(3.5, d_values[i] + 0.01, paste("d =", d_values[i]), 
         col = colors[i], cex = 0.7)
  }
  
  # Mark lower asymptote
  abline(h = guessing, lty = 2, col = "black", lwd = 2)
  text(-3.5, guessing + 0.02, paste("c =", guessing), col = "black", cex = 0.8)
  
  # Add effective range indicators
  for(i in 2:length(d_values)) {
    effective_range <- d_values[i] - guessing
    text(-2, d_values[i] - effective_range/2, 
         paste("Range:", round(effective_range, 2)), 
         col = colors[i], cex = 0.6, srt = 90)
  }
  
  legend("left", paste("d =", d_values), col = colors, lwd = 3, cex = 0.8)
  grid(TRUE)
  
  # Calculate key metrics
  cat("d Parametri Tesir Analizi:\n")
  for(i in 1:length(d_values)) {
    effective_range <- d_values[i] - guessing
    relative_range <- effective_range / (1.0 - guessing)
    
    cat(sprintf("d = %.2f: Effective range = %.2f (%.0f%% of max range)\n", 
                d_values[i], effective_range, 100 * relative_range))
  }
  
  return(list(theta = theta_range, d_values = d_values))
}

## === UPPER ASYMPTOTE DETECTION SIMULYASIYASI ===
simulate_upper_asymptote_detection <- function() {
  set.seed(4444)
  
  n_persons <- 1000
  n_items <- 15
  
  # Scenario: True 4PL data with clear upper asymptote
  theta_true <- rnorm(n_persons, 0, 1.2)
  
  # Item parameters with realistic upper asymptotes
  disc_true <- runif(n_items, 0.8, 2.0)
  diff_true <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)
  guess_true <- runif(n_items, 0.05, 0.25)
  upper_true <- runif(n_items, 0.80, 0.95)  # Clear upper asymptotes
  
  # Generate 4PL data
  data_4pl <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      prob <- prob_4pl(theta_true[i], disc_true[j], diff_true[j], 
                       guess_true[j], upper_true[j])
      data_4pl[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  # Detection analysis
  total_scores <- rowSums(data_4pl, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  # High ability analysis
  high_ability <- total_scores >= quantile(total_scores, 0.9)
  high_ability_performance <- colMeans(data_4pl[high_ability, ], na.rm = TRUE)
  
  cat("Upper Asymptote Detection Results:\n")
  cat("Sample size:", n_persons, "\n")
  cat("Items:", n_items, "\n")
  cat("True d range:", round(min(upper_true), 3), "-", round(max(upper_true), 3), "\n")
  cat("Mean true d:", round(mean(upper_true), 3), "\n\n")
  
  cat("High Ability Performance (top 10%):\n")
  cat("Mean performance:", round(mean(high_ability_performance), 3), "\n")
  cat("Max performance:", round(max(high_ability_performance), 3), "\n")
  
  # Evidence strength
  evidence_upper <- sum(high_ability_performance < 0.95) / length(high_ability_performance)
  cat("Items with evidence of upper asymptote (< 95%):", round(evidence_upper * 100, 1), "%\n")
  
  if(evidence_upper > 0.5) {
    cat("Strong evidence for upper asymptote - Consider 4PL\n")
  } else if(evidence_upper > 0.2) {
    cat("Moderate evidence for upper asymptote - Test 4PL\n")  
  } else {
    cat("Weak evidence for upper asymptote - 3PL likely sufficient\n")
  }
  
  return(list(
    data = data_4pl,
    true_params = list(theta = theta_true, disc = disc_true, diff = diff_true, 
                       guess = guess_true, upper = upper_true),
    high_ability_performance = high_ability_performance,
    evidence_strength = evidence_upper
  ))
}

cat("I(theta) â‰ˆ [a^2(d-c)^2*P(1-P)] / [(d-c)^2]\n")
## I(theta) â‰ˆ [a^2(d-c)^2*P(1-P)] / [(d-c)^2]

# Information function comparison across models
demonstrate_4pl_information <- function() {
  theta_range <- seq(-4, 4, by = 0.1)
  
  # Fixed parameters
  discrimination <- 1.5
  difficulty <- 0
  guessing <- 0.2
  
  # Different models
  upper_asymptotes <- c(1.0, 0.95, 0.90, 0.85, 0.80)
  colors <- c("blue", "green", "orange", "red", "purple")
  
  # Calculate information for different models
  info_1pl <- discrimination^2 * prob_1pl(theta_range, difficulty) * 
              (1 - prob_1pl(theta_range, difficulty))
  
  info_2pl <- discrimination^2 * prob_2pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty) * 
              (1 - prob_2pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty))
  
  info_3pl <- info_4pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, guessing, 1.0)
  
  # Plot base information (2PL for reference)
  plot(theta_range, info_2pl,
       type = "l", lwd = 2, col = "gray", lty = 2,
       main = "Model Information Comparison (a=1.5, b=0, c=0.2)",
       xlab = "Theta", ylab = "Information I(theta)",
       ylim = c(0, 0.6))
  
  # Add 3PL
  lines(theta_range, info_3pl, lwd = 3, col = "blue")
  
  # Add 4PL with different d values
  for(i in 2:length(upper_asymptotes)) {
    info_4pl_d <- info_4pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, 
                           guessing, upper_asymptotes[i])
    lines(theta_range, info_4pl_d, lwd = 3, col = colors[i])
  }
  
  legend("topright", 
         c("2PL (reference)", paste("4PL: d =", upper_asymptotes)), 
         col = c("gray", colors), 
         lwd = c(2, rep(3, length(colors))),
         lty = c(2, rep(1, length(colors))),
         cex = 0.8)
  
  grid(TRUE)
  
  # Calculate peak information for each model
  peak_info <- numeric(length(upper_asymptotes))
  peak_location <- numeric(length(upper_asymptotes))
  
  for(i in 1:length(upper_asymptotes)) {
    if(i == 1) {
      info_current <- info_3pl
    } else {
      info_current <- info_4pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, 
                               guessing, upper_asymptotes[i])
    }
    max_idx <- which.max(info_current)
    peak_info[i] <- info_current[max_idx]
    peak_location[i] <- theta_range[max_idx]
  }
  
  return(list(
    d_values = upper_asymptotes,
    peak_info = peak_info,
    peak_location = peak_location
  ))
}

## 
## === TEST INFORMATION SIMULYASIYA: MODEL COMPARISON ===
simulate_test_information_comparison <- function() {
  set.seed(5555)
  
  n_items <- 20
  theta_seq <- seq(-3, 3, by = 0.2)
  
  # Mixed item parameters - realistic for operational test
  discriminations <- runif(n_items, 0.8, 2.0)
  difficulties <- seq(-2.5, 2.5, length.out = n_items)
  guessing_params <- runif(n_items, 0.05, 0.25)
  upper_params <- runif(n_items, 0.85, 0.95)
  
  # Calculate test information for each model
  test_info_1pl <- numeric(length(theta_seq))
  test_info_2pl <- numeric(length(theta_seq))
  test_info_3pl <- numeric(length(theta_seq))
  test_info_4pl <- numeric(length(theta_seq))
  
  for(i in 1:length(theta_seq)) {
    theta <- theta_seq[i]
    
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      # 1PL (fixed discrimination = 1)
      p_1pl <- prob_1pl(theta, difficulties[j])
      test_info_1pl[i] <- test_info_1pl[i] + p_1pl * (1 - p_1pl)
      
      # 2PL
      p_2pl <- prob_2pl(theta, discriminations[j], difficulties[j])
      test_info_2pl[i] <- test_info_2pl[i] + discriminations[j]^2 * p_2pl * (1 - p_2pl)
      
      # 3PL
      info_3pl <- info_4pl(theta, discriminations[j], difficulties[j], 
                           guessing_params[j], 1.0)
      test_info_3pl[i] <- test_info_3pl[i] + info_3pl
      
      # 4PL
      info_4pl_item <- info_4pl(theta, discriminations[j], difficulties[j], 
                                guessing_params[j], upper_params[j])
      test_info_4pl[i] <- test_info_4pl[i] + info_4pl_item
    }
  }
  
  # Plot test information comparison
  plot(theta_seq, test_info_1pl, type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "black",
       main = "Test Information Comparison (20 items)",
       xlab = "Theta", ylab = "Test Information",
       ylim = c(0, max(test_info_2pl) * 1.1))
  
  lines(theta_seq, test_info_2pl, lwd = 3, col = "blue")
  lines(theta_seq, test_info_3pl, lwd = 3, col = "green")
  lines(theta_seq, test_info_4pl, lwd = 3, col = "red")
  
  legend("topright", c("1PL", "2PL", "3PL", "4PL"), 
         col = c("black", "blue", "green", "red"), lwd = 3)
  grid(TRUE)
  
  # Summary statistics
  max_info <- c(max(test_info_1pl), max(test_info_2pl), 
                max(test_info_3pl), max(test_info_4pl))
  optimal_theta <- c(theta_seq[which.max(test_info_1pl)],
                     theta_seq[which.max(test_info_2pl)],
                     theta_seq[which.max(test_info_3pl)],
                     theta_seq[which.max(test_info_4pl)])
  
  info_summary <- data.frame(
    Model = c("1PL", "2PL", "3PL", "4PL"),
    Max_Information = round(max_info, 2),
    Optimal_Theta = round(optimal_theta, 2),
    SE_at_Optimal = round(1/sqrt(max_info), 3),
    Info_Loss_vs_2PL = round((1 - max_info/max_info[2]) * 100, 1)
  )
  
  info_summary$Info_Loss_vs_2PL <- paste0(info_summary$Info_Loss_vs_2PL, "%")
  
  cat("Test Information Summary:\n")
  print(info_summary)
  
  # Information efficiency
  cat("\nInformation Efficiency Analysis:\n")
  cat("2PL -> 3PL loss:", round((1 - max_info[3]/max_info[2]) * 100, 1), "%\n")
  cat("3PL -> 4PL loss:", round((1 - max_info[4]/max_info[3]) * 100, 1), "%\n")
  cat("2PL -> 4PL total loss:", round((1 - max_info[4]/max_info[2]) * 100, 1), "%\n")
  
  return(list(
    theta = theta_seq,
    test_info = list(info_1pl = test_info_1pl, info_2pl = test_info_2pl,
                     info_3pl = test_info_3pl, info_4pl = test_info_4pl),
    summary = info_summary
  ))
}

# Simulate convergence problems
simulate_convergence_problems <- function() {
  cat("Convergence Problems Demonstration:\n\n")
  
  # Sample size effects on convergence
  sample_sizes <- c(200, 500, 1000, 1500, 2000, 3000)
  
  convergence_probs <- data.frame(
    Sample_Size = sample_sizes,
    One_PL = c(0.95, 0.98, 0.99, 0.99, 1.00, 1.00),
    Two_PL = c(0.80, 0.90, 0.95, 0.98, 0.99, 0.99),
    Three_PL = c(0.30, 0.60, 0.80, 0.90, 0.95, 0.98),
    Four_PL = c(0.05, 0.20, 0.40, 0.60, 0.75, 0.85)
  )
  
  print(convergence_probs)
  
  # Plot convergence probabilities
  plot(sample_sizes, convergence_probs$Four_PL, type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "red",
       main = "Model Convergence Probability vs Sample Size",
       xlab = "Sample Size", ylab = "Convergence Probability",
       ylim = c(0, 1))
  
  lines(sample_sizes, convergence_probs$Three_PL, lwd = 3, col = "green")
  lines(sample_sizes, convergence_probs$Two_PL, lwd = 3, col = "blue")
  lines(sample_sizes, convergence_probs$One_PL, lwd = 3, col = "black")
  
  abline(h = 0.8, lty = 2, col = "gray")
  text(1000, 0.82, "Acceptable threshold (80%)", cex = 0.8)
  
  legend("bottomright", c("1PL", "2PL", "3PL", "4PL"), 
         col = c("black", "blue", "green", "red"), lwd = 3)
  grid(TRUE)
  
  # Minimum sample size recommendations
  min_sample_4pl <- sample_sizes[which(convergence_probs$Four_PL >= 0.8)[1]]
  min_sample_3pl <- sample_sizes[which(convergence_probs$Three_PL >= 0.8)[1]]
  
  cat("\nMinimum Sample Size for 80% Convergence:\n")
  cat("3PL:", min_sample_3pl, "\n")
  cat("4PL:", min_sample_4pl, "\n")
  cat("4PL needs", round(min_sample_4pl/min_sample_3pl, 1), "x more data than 3PL\n\n")
  
  return(convergence_probs)
}

# Parameter correlation analysis
parameter_correlation_analysis <- function() {
  cat("4PL Parameter Correlation Matrix (typical values):\n\n")
  
  # Theoretical correlation matrix based on literature
  param_corr_matrix <- matrix(c(
    1.00, 0.15, -0.80, 0.60,  # a correlations
    0.15, 1.00, -0.20, -0.25, # b correlations
    -0.80, -0.20, 1.00, -0.85, # c correlations
    0.60, -0.25, -0.85, 1.00   # d correlations
  ), nrow = 4, byrow = TRUE)
  
  rownames(param_corr_matrix) <- c("a (disc)", "b (diff)", "c (guess)", "d (upper)")
  colnames(param_corr_matrix) <- c("a", "b", "c", "d")
  
  print(round(param_corr_matrix, 2))
  
  cat("\nCritical Correlations:\n")
  cat("c - d correlation: -0.85 (very high negative)\n")
  cat("a - c correlation: -0.80 (high negative)\n") 
  cat("a - d correlation: 0.60 (moderate positive)\n\n")
  
  cat("Consequences:\n")
  cat("â€¢ c ve d arasinda trade-off\n")
  cat("â€¢ a parametri c ve d ile kompensasiya\n")
  cat("â€¢ Estimation cox qeyri-sabit\n")
  cat("â€¢ Large standard errors\n")
  cat("â€¢ Singular Hessian matrix risk\n\n")
  
  # Demonstrate parameter compensation
  cat("Parameter Compensation Effects:\n")
  
  # Example: same ICC with different parameter combinations
  theta_range <- seq(-3, 3, by = 0.5)
  
  # Scenario 1: c=0.2, d=0.9
  params1 <- list(a = 1.5, b = 0, c = 0.2, d = 0.9)
  prob1 <- prob_4pl(theta_range, params1$a, params1$b, params1$c, params1$d)
  
  # Scenario 2: c=0.15, d=0.85 (compensated)
  params2 <- list(a = 1.8, b = 0.1, c = 0.15, d = 0.85)
  prob2 <- prob_4pl(theta_range, params2$a, params2$b, params2$c, params2$d)
  
  compensation_demo <- data.frame(
    Theta = theta_range,
    Scenario_1 = round(prob1, 3),
    Scenario_2 = round(prob2, 3),
    Difference = round(abs(prob1 - prob2), 4)
  )
  
  cat("Parameter Compensation Example:\n")
  cat("Scenario 1: a=1.5, b=0, c=0.20, d=0.90\n")
  cat("Scenario 2: a=1.8, b=0.1, c=0.15, d=0.85\n\n")
  
  print(compensation_demo)
  
  max_diff <- max(compensation_demo$Difference)
  cat("\nMaximum probability difference:", max_diff, "\n")
  if(max_diff < 0.05) {
    cat("- Very similar ICCs despite different parameters!\n")
    cat("- This is why 4PL estimation is so difficult\n")
  }
  
  return(param_corr_matrix)
}

# Generate realistic 4PL data for analysis
generate_4pl_data <- function() {
  set.seed(6666)
  
  n_persons <- 1200  # Large sample for 4PL
  n_items <- 15      # Moderate number of items
  
  # Person abilities
  theta_true <- rnorm(n_persons, mean = 0, sd = 1.1)
  
  # Item parameters - realistic 4PL scenario
  disc_true <- runif(n_items, 0.8, 2.0)
  diff_true <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)
  guess_true <- runif(n_items, 0.05, 0.25)
  # Upper asymptotes suggesting ceiling effects
  upper_true <- rbeta(n_items, shape1 = 8, shape2 = 1) * 0.25 + 0.75  # Range: 0.75-1.0
  
  # Generate 4PL data
  data_4pl <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      prob <- prob_4pl(theta_true[i], disc_true[j], diff_true[j], 
                       guess_true[j], upper_true[j])
      data_4pl[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  colnames(data_4pl) <- paste0("Item", 1:n_items)
  
  return(list(
    data = data_4pl,
    true_params = list(
      theta = theta_true,
      discrimination = disc_true,
      difficulty = diff_true,
      guessing = guess_true,
      upper_asymptote = upper_true
    ),
    specifications = list(
      n_persons = n_persons,
      n_items = n_items,
      context = "Simulated 4PL data"
    )
  ))
}

# mirt paketi ile 4PL analizi
perform_4pl_mirt_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== MIRT 4PL ANALIZI:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  if(!require(mirt, quietly = TRUE)) {
    cat("mirt paketi movcud deyil.\n")
    return(NULL)
  }
  
  tryCatch({
    cat("MIRT model fitting: 1PL, 2PL, 3PL, 4PL...\n")
    cat("Xeberdarliq: 4PL fitting uzun ceke biler ve convergence problemi ola biler\n\n")
    
    # Fit models progressively
    model_1pl_mirt <- mirt(data, 1, itemtype = "Rasch", verbose = FALSE)
    cat("1PL fitted successfully\n")
    
    model_2pl_mirt <- mirt(data, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
    cat("2PL fitted successfully\n")
    
    model_3pl_mirt <- mirt(data, 1, itemtype = "3PL", verbose = FALSE)
    cat("3PL fitted successfully\n")
    
    # 4PL with constraints to improve convergence
    model_4pl_mirt <- mirt(data, 1, itemtype = "4PL", verbose = FALSE)
    cat("4PL fitting attempted...\n")
    
    cat("All models fitted.\n\n")
    
    # Model comparison
    cat("=== MIRT MODEL MUQAYISE ===\n")
    
    # Extract fit statistics
    fit_1pl <- extract.mirt(model_1pl_mirt, "fit")
    fit_2pl <- extract.mirt(model_2pl_mirt, "fit")
    fit_3pl <- extract.mirt(model_3pl_mirt, "fit")
    fit_4pl <- extract.mirt(model_4pl_mirt, "fit")
    
    mirt_fit_comparison <- data.frame(
      Model = c("1PL", "2PL", "3PL", "4PL"),
      LogLik = round(c(fit_1pl["logLik"], fit_2pl["logLik"], 
                       fit_3pl["logLik"], fit_4pl["logLik"]), 2),
      AIC = round(c(fit_1pl["AIC"], fit_2pl["AIC"], 
                    fit_3pl["AIC"], fit_4pl["AIC"]), 2),
      BIC = round(c(fit_1pl["BIC"], fit_2pl["BIC"], 
                    fit_3pl["BIC"], fit_4pl["BIC"]), 2),
      Parameters = c(ncol(data) + 1, 2*ncol(data) + 1, 
                     3*ncol(data) + 1, 4*ncol(data) + 1)
    )
    
    print(mirt_fit_comparison)
    
    # Best models
    best_aic <- mirt_fit_comparison$Model[which.min(mirt_fit_comparison$AIC)]
    best_bic <- mirt_fit_comparison$Model[which.min(mirt_fit_comparison$BIC)]
    
    cat("\nBest model by AIC:", best_aic, "\n")
    cat("Best model by BIC:", best_bic, "\n")
    
    # Model comparison tests
    cat("\n=== MODEL COMPARISON TESTS ===\n")
    
    tryCatch({
      comparison_4pl_3pl <- anova(model_3pl_mirt, model_4pl_mirt)
      cat("4PL vs 3PL Comparison:\n")
      print(comparison_4pl_3pl)
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("4PL vs 3PL comparison failed:", e$message, "\n")
    })
    
    # 4PL parameters
    cat("\n=== 4PL PARAMETRLERI ===\n")
    
    params_4pl_mirt <- coef(model_4pl_mirt, simplify = TRUE)
    item_params_mirt <- params_4pl_mirt$items
    
    # Check if 4PL parameters are available
    if("u" %in% colnames(item_params_mirt)) {
      mirt_4pl_params_table <- data.frame(
        Item = 1:nrow(item_params_mirt),
        Discrimination = round(item_params_mirt[, "a1"], 3),
        Difficulty = round(-item_params_mirt[, "d"] / item_params_mirt[, "a1"], 3),
        Guessing = round(item_params_mirt[, "g"], 3),
        Upper_Asymptote = round(item_params_mirt[, "u"], 3),
        Effective_Range = round(item_params_mirt[, "u"] - item_params_mirt[, "g"], 3)
      )
      
      print(head(mirt_4pl_params_table, 10))
      
      # Parameter diagnostics
      cat("\n4PL Parameter Diagnostics:\n")
      
      # Check for boundary estimates
      boundary_g <- sum(mirt_4pl_params_table$Guessing < 0.001 | 
                       mirt_4pl_params_table$Guessing > 0.49)
      boundary_u <- sum(mirt_4pl_params_table$Upper_Asymptote > 0.999)
      small_range <- sum(mirt_4pl_params_table$Effective_Range < 0.3)
      
      cat("Boundary guessing estimates (<=0.001 or >=0.49):", boundary_g, "\n")
      cat("Boundary upper estimates (>=0.999):", boundary_u, "\n")
      cat("Small effective range (<0.3):", small_range, "\n")
      
      # Parameter summary
      cat("\n4PL Parameter Summary:\n")
      cat("Discrimination: Mean =", round(mean(mirt_4pl_params_table$Discrimination), 3), 
          ", Range =", round(min(mirt_4pl_params_table$Discrimination), 3), "-",
          round(max(mirt_4pl_params_table$Discrimination), 3), "\n")
      
      cat("Guessing: Mean =", round(mean(mirt_4pl_params_table$Guessing), 3), 
          ", Range =", round(min(mirt_4pl_params_table$Guessing), 3), "-",
          round(max(mirt_4pl_params_table$Guessing), 3), "\n")
      
      cat("Upper asymptote: Mean =", round(mean(mirt_4pl_params_table$Upper_Asymptote), 3), 
          ", Range =", round(min(mirt_4pl_params_table$Upper_Asymptote), 3), "-",
          round(max(mirt_4pl_params_table$Upper_Asymptote), 3), "\n")
      
      cat("Effective range: Mean =", round(mean(mirt_4pl_params_table$Effective_Range), 3), 
          ", Range =", round(min(mirt_4pl_params_table$Effective_Range), 3), "-",
          round(max(mirt_4pl_params_table$Effective_Range), 3), "\n")
      
      # Quality assessment
      high_quality_4pl <- sum(mirt_4pl_params_table$Discrimination > 1.0 & 
                             mirt_4pl_params_table$Effective_Range > 0.4)
      problematic_4pl <- sum(mirt_4pl_params_table$Discrimination < 0.8 | 
                            mirt_4pl_params_table$Effective_Range < 0.3)
      
      cat("\nItem Quality Assessment (4PL):\n")
      cat("High quality items (a > 1.0, range > 0.4):", high_quality_4pl, "/", nrow(mirt_4pl_params_table), "\n")
      cat("Problematic items (a < 0.8 or range < 0.3):", problematic_4pl, "/", nrow(mirt_4pl_params_table), "\n")
      
      estimation_issues <- list(
        boundary_g = boundary_g, 
        boundary_u = boundary_u, 
        small_range = small_range
      )
      
    } else {
      cat("4PL parameters not available (estimation may have failed)\n")
      mirt_4pl_params_table <- NULL
      estimation_issues <- list(estimation_failed = TRUE)
    }
    
    return(list(
      model_1pl = model_1pl_mirt,
      model_2pl = model_2pl_mirt,
      model_3pl = model_3pl_mirt,
      model_4pl = model_4pl_mirt,
      fit_comparison = mirt_fit_comparison,
      item_params_4pl = mirt_4pl_params_table,
      best_model_aic = best_aic,
      best_model_bic = best_bic,
      estimation_issues = estimation_issues
    ))
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("MIRT 4PL analysis xetasi:", e$message, "\n")
    cat("Bu 4PL modelinin tipik estimation problemidir\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
}

  )
  
  print(cost_benefit)
